wikipedia_page.main: Henry Grey Tylecote (24 July 1853 – 8 March 1935) was an English first-class cricketer and educator. Tylecote appeared in 29 first-class matches between 1874 and 1886, playing the majority of these for Oxford University, as well as appearing for the Marylebone Cricket Club amongst others.
